{"parentUuid": "ee4c0841-3c4e-498b-ac2b-8a13759c025e", "isSidechain": false, "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "tool_result", "tool_use_id": "toolu_455af237-0b90-42", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{{ config(materialized='incremental', unique_key='event_id') }}\n\nSELECT\n  event_id,\n  event_date,\n  user_id,\n  revenue\nFROM {{ source('raw', 'events') }}\n\n{% if is_incremental() %}\nWHERE event_date > (SELECT max(event_date) FROM {{ this }})\n{% endif %}\n"}]}]}, "uuid": "6c2ab542-5711-49ee-a2fb-cf71dd6537d2", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T16:00:37.000Z", "isMeta": true, "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/data-pipeline", "sessionId": "ad4da2e7-d24d-464d-80e5-5df79e89f526", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
{"parentUuid": "6c2ab542-5711-49ee-a2fb-cf71dd6537d2", "isSidechain": false, "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-7", "id": "msg_57f58a68-dc5", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Backfills don't play well with `event_date > max(event_date)` \u2014 once you've inserted today's data, a backfill of yesterday's data is filtered out because `max(event_date)` is now today. Two clean fixes: (1) replace `>` with a sliding window \u2014 `WHERE event_date >= dateadd(day, -3, current_date)` if you only ever backfill within 3 days; or (2) switch the model to `incremental_strategy='merge'` (with `unique_key='event_id'` which you already have) and drop the `is_incremental` predicate entirely \u2014 let dbt's merge handle dedupe by key. Option 2 is more expensive but bulletproof."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"input_tokens": 159, "output_tokens": 304, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}}, "requestId": "req_d5f95e2c-cff", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "220f0cc6-3973-485b-8ba7-06bdde5ffb8a", "timestamp": "2026-05-05T16:00:43.000Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/data-pipeline", "sessionId": "ad4da2e7-d24d-464d-80e5-5df79e89f526", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
